## Frequently Asked Questions

### How is the gravel quantity calculated?
The app takes your excavation floor dimensions (length × width × depth), adjusts the total volume for the protective system you select (vertical/shored, sloped, or benched walls), subtracts the volume of the tanks you enter, and converts the remaining volume to tons using the gravel density you set.

### What do the protective system options mean?
These follow OSHA 1926 Subpart P excavation classifications:
- **Vertical / Shored** — walls are supported and cut straight down; the hole stays at the entered dimensions.
- **Sloped** — walls are cut back at the maximum allowable slope for your soil type (Type A ¾:1, Type B 1:1, Type C 1½:1), widening the opening and increasing gravel volume.
- **Benched** — walls are stepped, with an adjustable bench height. Note: OSHA does not permit benching in Type C soil.

### What waste factor should I use?
Typical values are 5–10% for pea gravel and 10–15% for compacted crushed rock. Use the higher end for wet conditions or soft subgrades. The Recommended Order figure includes this factor.

### Does the app need an internet connection?
No. All calculations run entirely on your device and the app works fully offline.

### Does the app collect my data?
No. See our [Privacy Policy](PRIVACY_POLICY.md) — the app collects no data of any kind.

### How do I remove a tank from the calculation?
Swipe left on the tank row in the Fuel Tanks section.

## Disclaimer

Tank Install Calculator provides material estimates for planning purposes. Always verify quantities, soil classifications, and excavation safety requirements with a qualified engineer and your local regulations before ordering material or beginning work.
